all my hard drinking.

00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:28.356 position:50% align:center
Let's see some hands!

00:02:28.440 --> 00:02:30.900 position:50% align:center
Which of you kids are just
bursting with energy today?

00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:32.485 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Me!

00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.529 position:50% align:center
Cool, and who's
just feeling okay?

00:02:34.612 --> 00:02:36.281 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Me!

00:02:36.364 --> 00:02:37.991 position:50% align:center
Who's in pain? Fatigued?

00:02:38.074 --> 00:02:40.744 position:50% align:center
Frayed like a dog's
favorite toy?

00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:45.081 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Me...

00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:48.335 position:50% align:center
Interesting. Just me, huh?

00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:49.252 position:50% align:center
Well, well.

00:02:49.336 --> 00:02:53.173 position:50% align:center
[YUKA grunting]

00:02:56.092 --> 00:02:57.510 position:50% align:center
Oh, Hello, Yuka- <i>chan</i> .

00:02:57.594 --> 00:03:00.305 position:50% align:center
What's with the surprise
attack? Wanna chat?

00:03:00.388 --> 00:03:04.225 position:50% align:center
I was just casting a spell to
help you feel better, Oniisan!

00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:05.977 position:50% align:center
That's nice.

00:03:07.520 --> 00:03:08.605 position:50% align:center
Ya know what?

00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:10.023 position:50% align:center
Yuka- <i>chan</i> just inspired me

00:03:10.106 --> 00:03:12.567 position:50% align:center
to cast a special
spell on all of you!

00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:14.944 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
What kinda spell will it be?

00:03:15.028 --> 00:03:16.821 position:50% align:center
It's a spell of preservation.

00:03:16.905 --> 00:03:18.281 position:50% align:center
With any luck,
it'll save you kids

00:03:18.365 --> 00:03:21.242 position:50% align:center
from ending up like
me in 20 years.

00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:27.415 position:50% align:center
[EDEI] Okay, cut!
Let's take a quick break.

00:03:27.499 --> 00:03:30.001 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
<i>Uramichi Oniisan</i> !

00:03:30.085 --> 00:03:34.339 position:50% align:center
[KIDS laughing]

00:03:34.422 --> 00:03:36.091 position:50% align:center
Hi! Welcome back, kids!

00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:38.468 position:50% align:center
We should sing the
ABC Song right now,

00:03:38.551 --> 00:03:41.513 position:50% align:center
but there's been a
little change of plans.

00:03:41.596 --> 00:03:44.307 position:50% align:center
I've decided to teach you
the Uramichi Song instead!

00:03:44.391 --> 00:03:45.850 position:50% align:center
It's a fun little protest song.

00:03:45.934 --> 00:03:49.521 position:50% align:center
I wrote the music and
lyrics all by myself!

00:03:49.604 --> 00:03:52.524 position:50% align:center
Let's not worry about coming up
with a new exercise for it.

00:03:52.607 --> 00:03:55.110 position:50% align:center
Just follow my lead and
we'll feel it out as we go.

00:03:55.193 --> 00:03:58.154 position:50% align:center
Wait, so why aren't we gonna
do the ABC Song today?

00:03:58.238 --> 00:04:01.616 position:50% align:center
I don't wanna do another song.

00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:04.577 position:50% align:center
Because [bleep]RAC needs to
know that I'm pissed off.

00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:07.038 position:50% align:center
JAS(bleep) is like an octopus
that loves sweet treats,

00:04:07.122 --> 00:04:10.166 position:50% align:center
who sticks his gross tentacles
into other people's cookie jars.

00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:12.210 position:50% align:center
And with his mouth full,
says, "You're welcome, bud.

00:04:12.293 --> 00:04:13.878 position:50% align:center
I made sure no one else
would eat your cookies.

00:04:13.962 --> 00:04:15.088 position:50% align:center
Aren't you glad
I have a monopoly

00:04:15.171 --> 00:04:17.507 position:50% align:center
on the copyright
collection business?"

00:04:20.427 --> 00:04:22.095 position:50% align:center
Everyone ready?

00:04:22.178 --> 00:04:24.139 position:50% align:center
'Kay! Let's go!

00:04:24.222 --> 00:04:25.890 position:50% align:center
The "U" in Uramichi.

00:04:25.974 --> 00:04:28.059 position:50% align:center
[KIDS] ♪ "U's" for
feeling unfulfilled! ♪

00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:29.686 position:50% align:center
Right! But what
about the "Ra"?

00:04:29.769 --> 00:04:31.938 position:50% align:center
[KIDS] ♪ "Ra's" for
rather do nothing! ♪

00:04:32.022 --> 00:04:33.940 position:50% align:center
You know me well!
Now what about the "mi"?

00:04:34.024 --> 00:04:36.943 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
♪ "Mi" is for misery. ♪

00:04:37.027 --> 00:04:38.236 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
And "chi"!

00:04:38.319 --> 00:04:40.447 position:50% align:center
[KIDS] ♪ "Chi" is for
the chill in my soul! ♪

00:04:40.530 --> 00:04:42.323 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Mh-hm.

00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:44.492 position:50% align:center
Excellent work!

00:04:44.576 --> 00:04:47.328 position:50% align:center
That was super impressive,
kids, seriously!

00:04:47.412 --> 00:04:49.039 position:50% align:center
As boring as that
was for you tykes,

00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:51.583 position:50% align:center
you still managed
to feign interest!

00:04:51.666 --> 00:04:53.376 position:50% align:center
Keep honing that skill,
'cause when ya grow up

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:56.546 position:50% align:center
and enter the workforce,
you're gonna need it.

00:04:56.629 --> 00:04:58.381 position:50% align:center
Hey, Uramichi Oniisan!

00:04:58.465 --> 00:05:00.925 position:50% align:center
What does "enter the
workforce" even mean?

00:05:01.009 --> 00:05:02.177 position:50% align:center
It's a crossroads.

00:05:02.260 --> 00:05:03.887 position:50% align:center
A point at which
society expects you

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:07.015 position:50% align:center
to make big choices that'll
dictate the rest of your life.

00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:08.725 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah?

00:05:08.808 --> 00:05:10.977 position:50% align:center
You'll be mocked,
rejected, and shot down.

00:05:11.061 --> 00:05:12.854 position:50% align:center
Not only when you're
hunting for a job,

00:05:12.937 --> 00:05:14.647 position:50% align:center
but for half your adult life!

00:05:14.731 --> 00:05:15.899 position:50% align:center
Just keep your chin up

00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:18.777 position:50% align:center
and never lose sight of
who you are, understand?

00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:20.445 position:50% align:center
Keep a list of the people
who've wronged you

00:05:20.528 --> 00:05:23.323 position:50% align:center
and never forget that Oniisan's
favorite little siblings

00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:25.700 position:50% align:center
are the ones who can throw
a good sucker-punch.

00:05:25.784 --> 00:05:27.744 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Uhh...

00:05:30.622 --> 00:05:33.667 position:50% align:center
[EDEI]
Okay, cut! We're movin' on!

00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:35.210 position:50% align:center
I'll see you next time!

00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:37.712 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Bye!

00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:40.048 position:50% align:center
'Kay, so we're bringin'
in a different set of kids

00:05:40.131 --> 00:05:41.257 position:50% align:center
for the next segment.

00:05:41.341 --> 00:05:43.176 position:50% align:center
Feel free to rest up
while we prep 'em, cool?

00:05:43.259 --> 00:05:44.469 position:50% align:center
Sure!

00:05:44.552 --> 00:05:46.846 position:50% align:center
You're doin' great,
Uramichi, just keep it up!

00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:49.265 position:50% align:center
Thanks a million. I sure will.

00:05:54.562 --> 00:05:56.022 position:50% align:center
Huh? Ah!

00:05:56.106 --> 00:05:58.775 position:50% align:center
It's Uramichi Oniisan!

00:05:58.858 --> 00:06:00.610 position:50% align:center
Are you going home,
too, big brother?

00:06:00.694 --> 00:06:02.987 position:50% align:center
No, I'm just taking
a break right now.

00:06:03.071 --> 00:06:04.364 position:50% align:center
[GIRL D]
How come?

00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:05.949 position:50% align:center
You know how you don't
feel like playing

00:06:06.032 --> 00:06:08.034 position:50% align:center
if you can't get your
rest at naptime?

00:06:08.118 --> 00:06:09.828 position:50% align:center
Well, if my facial
muscles can't rest,

00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.831 position:50% align:center
they'll start twitching
till they die.

00:06:12.914 --> 00:06:16.001 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
<i>Uramichi Oniisan</i> !

00:06:17.919 --> 00:06:19.921 position:50% align:center
[KIDS laughing]

00:06:20.005 --> 00:06:21.589 position:50% align:center
Hi!

00:06:21.673 --> 00:06:24.551 position:50% align:center
Let's start today's episode
of <i>Together with Maman</i> !

00:06:24.634 --> 00:06:26.469 position:50% align:center
Oh, but before all that,

00:06:26.553 --> 00:06:28.096 position:50% align:center
I've been told that
little Miki- <i>chan</i>

00:06:28.179 --> 00:06:29.973 position:50% align:center
wants to ask me a question!

00:06:30.056 --> 00:06:31.891 position:50% align:center
What could it be?

00:06:33.309 --> 00:06:35.729 position:50% align:center
Go on. Ask away.

00:06:35.812 --> 00:06:37.981 position:50% align:center
[MIKI] Um. How old
are you, Oniisan?

00:06:38.064 --> 00:06:39.774 position:50% align:center
A little over 31.

00:06:39.858 --> 00:06:41.276 position:50% align:center
[MIKI]
Really?

00:06:41.359 --> 00:06:42.736 position:50% align:center
My dad's 29, so that means

00:06:42.819 --> 00:06:44.821 position:50% align:center
you're a lot older
than him, right?

00:06:44.904 --> 00:06:47.032 position:50% align:center
Isn't it a little weird that
you haven't gotten married

00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:49.659 position:50% align:center
or become a daddy
in all that time?

00:06:51.870 --> 00:06:54.456 position:50% align:center
Cut me some slack, would ya?

00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.791 position:50% align:center
Okay, sure. Learning moment.

00:06:56.875 --> 00:06:59.544 position:50% align:center
No person's life will be
quite like any others.

00:06:59.627 --> 00:07:01.046 position:50% align:center
So just 'cause a guy
tends to spend

00:07:01.129 --> 00:07:02.464 position:50% align:center
his evenings alone at home,

00:07:02.547 --> 00:07:05.133 position:50% align:center
downing cheap saké and
watching unfunny sitcoms,

00:07:05.216 --> 00:07:08.470 position:50% align:center
doesn't mean he's some
kind of depressed misfit.

00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:09.763 position:50% align:center
Words can kill people.

00:07:09.846 --> 00:07:11.890 position:50% align:center
So keep your judgy
thoughts to yourself.

00:07:11.973 --> 00:07:13.433 position:50% align:center
Sorry, but I don't
really understand

00:07:13.516 --> 00:07:15.185 position:50% align:center
what you're talking about.

00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:17.103 position:50% align:center
Neither do I.

00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:22.484 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
I'm falling apart...

00:07:22.567 --> 00:07:24.152 position:50% align:center
[wailing]

00:07:24.235 --> 00:07:26.988 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Hm? It's Tomoki- <i>kun</i> , right?

00:07:27.072 --> 00:07:30.742 position:50% align:center
Didja trip and fall?
That must hurt, huh?

00:07:30.825 --> 00:07:34.579 position:50% align:center
Okay. Let's get your
mind off it, pal.

00:07:34.662 --> 00:07:37.248 position:50% align:center
What happened to my smile
and my will to live?

00:07:37.332 --> 00:07:39.626 position:50% align:center
Where are they now?

00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:41.961 position:50% align:center
Gone.

00:07:42.045 --> 00:07:45.215 position:50% align:center
When you grow up, you'll have
to make yourself stop crying.

00:07:45.298 --> 00:07:46.925 position:50% align:center
Act too sad and
the people you love

00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:49.344 position:50% align:center
will pry you off like a tick.

00:07:53.848 --> 00:07:55.767 position:50% align:center
Now! Let's call in our friends,

00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:58.645 position:50% align:center
Usao- <i>kun</i> the bunny and
Kumao- <i>kun</i> the bear!

00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:00.230 position:50% align:center
And go!

00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:04.818 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI, KIDS]
Usao- <i>kun</i> ! Kumao- <i>kun</i> !

00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:09.155 position:50% align:center
Huh, well, that's odd!

00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:11.866 position:50% align:center
Maybe they aren't as
good at Japanese as us.

00:08:11.950 --> 00:08:15.787 position:50% align:center
Let's call for them in
English, okay? And go!

00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:20.750 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI, KIDS]
Mister Bunny! Mister Bear!

00:08:23.753 --> 00:08:26.840 position:50% align:center
Still no sign of those two.
What's the deal?

00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:29.259 position:50% align:center
I guess we just weren't
loud enough that time.

00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:33.346 position:50% align:center
Let's give it one
more try! And go!

00:08:33.430 --> 00:08:34.097 position:50% align:center
Mister B--

00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:35.015 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI coughing]

00:08:35.098 --> 00:08:37.183 position:50% align:center
[GIRL A]
Are you okay, Oniisan?

00:08:37.267 --> 00:08:39.269 position:50% align:center
[GIRL B]
Is it the drinking?

00:08:45.108 --> 00:08:48.903 position:50% align:center
I said to start coming out
the second time we call.

00:08:48.987 --> 00:08:50.739 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] But the script
says we should come out

00:08:50.822 --> 00:08:53.241 position:50% align:center
the third time you call.

00:08:53.324 --> 00:08:56.745 position:50% align:center
Scripts come and go,
but I've only got one throat.

00:08:56.828 --> 00:09:00.373 position:50% align:center
[GOD] Uramichi Omota,
31 years old. Single.

00:09:00.457 --> 00:09:03.835 position:50% align:center
He works as a gymnast Oniisan.

00:09:03.918 --> 00:09:05.211 position:50% align:center
As an award-winning gymnast

00:09:05.295 --> 00:09:07.630 position:50% align:center
with a degree in
physical education,

00:09:07.714 --> 00:09:10.383 position:50% align:center
his body is extremely
stable and balanced.

00:09:10.467 --> 00:09:14.012 position:50% align:center
Especially... when compared
to his emotional state.

00:09:14.095 --> 00:09:16.681 position:50% align:center
As of late, whenever
I raise my voice,

00:09:16.765 --> 00:09:21.269 position:50% align:center
I kinda feel something
get torn away.

00:09:21.353 --> 00:09:23.355 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
What's that?

00:09:23.438 --> 00:09:25.398 position:50% align:center
My soul.

00:09:27.359 --> 00:09:31.071 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] I don't get it.
Why does he still work here?

00:09:31.154 --> 00:09:32.989 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Uramichi, you were a hero

00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:34.866 position:50% align:center
at Sports Science University.

00:09:34.949 --> 00:09:38.912 position:50% align:center
As your juniors,
we both looked up to you.

00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:42.582 position:50% align:center
But now... Well, remember
what Professor Anzai told us?

00:09:42.665 --> 00:09:43.708 position:50% align:center
"If you give up early,

00:09:43.792 --> 00:09:46.419 position:50% align:center
the game'll be over
before it starts."

00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:51.341 position:50% align:center
But it turns out there
are some games that go on

00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:53.885 position:50% align:center
long after you've given up.

00:09:53.968 --> 00:09:57.389 position:50% align:center
Like the game we call "life."

00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:00.100 position:50% align:center
[EDEI]
That's a wrap for the day!

00:10:00.183 --> 00:10:02.602 position:50% align:center
Way to go, everyone!
Good hustle!

00:10:03.645 --> 00:10:06.356 position:50% align:center
Where's our star?
He comin' out tonight?

00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:08.608 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Heh. Doubt it.
He's already gone home.

00:10:08.692 --> 00:10:12.570 position:50% align:center
Yeah. He does tend to be
the first one gone, huh?

00:10:18.785 --> 00:10:21.246 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
You could call me two-faced,

00:10:21.329 --> 00:10:24.165 position:50% align:center
but every adult has
a hidden side.

00:10:30.255 --> 00:10:32.132 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Don't rat me out.

00:10:32.215 --> 00:10:36.386 position:50% align:center
Just pretend you didn't
see, okay, kids?

00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:40.181 position:50% align:center
[alarm beeping]

00:10:47.731 --> 00:10:52.068 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] Why? Why does
the sun keep rising?

00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:56.197 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Welp, I don't know about you,

00:10:56.281 --> 00:10:58.658 position:50% align:center
but I'm raring for
some ABC calesthenics!

00:10:58.742 --> 00:11:00.118 position:50% align:center
Why not the [bleep]RAC Song?

00:11:00.201 --> 00:11:01.745 position:50% align:center
Are you not fighting
them anymore?

00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:04.706 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] That wasn't a fight.
It was a reckless provocation.

00:11:04.789 --> 00:11:07.042 position:50% align:center
Did I abandon my
principles overnight?

00:11:07.125 --> 00:11:09.461 position:50% align:center
Yes, because that's what
grown-ups do when they're weak.

00:11:09.544 --> 00:11:10.920 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:14.132 position:50% align:center
Good. Good. Now gather
around, everybody!

00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:15.967 position:50% align:center
[GIRL A] Is that your
real voice, Oniisan?

00:11:16.051 --> 00:11:17.802 position:50% align:center
Are you asking me if
I have to force myself

00:11:17.886 --> 00:11:19.554 position:50% align:center
to sound this
relentlessly cheerful?

00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:21.389 position:50% align:center
No way, I'm happy!

00:11:21.473 --> 00:11:22.390 position:50% align:center
[BOY D laughs]

00:11:22.474 --> 00:11:24.267 position:50% align:center
That wasn't a joke,
ya lil goober.

00:11:24.351 --> 00:11:27.395 position:50% align:center
Hey, Oniisan! Did something
good happen to you today?

00:11:27.479 --> 00:11:28.688 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Of course not!

00:11:28.772 --> 00:11:29.272 position:50% align:center
"Of course not!"

00:11:29.356 --> 00:11:30.857 position:50% align:center
Also not a joke!

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.400 position:50% align:center
But if nothing good
happened to you,

00:11:32.484 --> 00:11:34.277 position:50% align:center
then why are you smiling so big?

00:11:34.361 --> 00:11:36.196 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] It's precisely
because I have nothing else

00:11:36.279 --> 00:11:37.864 position:50% align:center
going for me that
I need to smile!

00:11:37.947 --> 00:11:39.282 position:50% align:center
Oh.

00:11:39.366 --> 00:11:41.117 position:50% align:center
Behind my smile is the
knowledge that after this shoot,

00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:43.036 position:50% align:center
I'll retire to a lifeless,
empty home,

00:11:43.119 --> 00:11:45.413 position:50% align:center
where I'll sit and numbly wonder
why playing with you kids

00:11:45.497 --> 00:11:48.458 position:50% align:center
is the only thing that
makes me feel alive.

00:11:48.541 --> 00:11:51.252 position:50% align:center
That last part was a joke!

00:11:51.336 --> 00:11:53.213 position:50% align:center
I may be alone, but I don't
think that makes me

00:11:53.296 --> 00:11:56.508 position:50% align:center
some kind of anti-social
creep who's failing at life.

00:11:56.591 --> 00:11:59.678 position:50% align:center
