boyfriend for over five years.

00:17:07.235 --> 00:17:09.195 position:50% align:center
I gotta get married.

00:17:11.573 --> 00:17:12.782 position:50% align:center
You hear me?

00:17:12.866 --> 00:17:17.078 position:50% align:center
Huh? 'Fraid not.
Had something on my mind.

00:17:19.330 --> 00:17:23.043 position:50% align:center
[EDEI]
And cut! Such a good hustle!

00:17:24.169 --> 00:17:26.838 position:50% align:center
Take yourself a break while we
set up for the next session!

00:17:26.921 --> 00:17:28.965 position:50% align:center
Sure!

00:17:29.049 --> 00:17:32.260 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Seriously, Uramichi is so-- Uh!

00:17:39.184 --> 00:17:42.228 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] Suspicious and rude
as he's acting right now,

00:17:42.312 --> 00:17:45.065 position:50% align:center
I just don't have the energy
to deal with him.

00:17:45.148 --> 00:17:49.486 position:50% align:center
This is heartbreaking.
I must be nearing my end.

00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:50.570 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Nothing?

00:17:50.653 --> 00:17:52.906 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
I'm even more scared now.

00:17:59.788 --> 00:18:01.456 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
As best I can tell,

00:18:01.539 --> 00:18:05.168 position:50% align:center
it's when you stop fighting
that you start getting old.

00:18:05.251 --> 00:18:06.961 position:50% align:center
I don't mean that literally.

00:18:07.045 --> 00:18:09.881 position:50% align:center
It's more a question of
spirit than aggression.

00:18:09.964 --> 00:18:13.510 position:50% align:center
Struggle, hardship, and
competition help people grow.

00:18:13.593 --> 00:18:16.304 position:50% align:center
Even when we eat dirt.

00:18:16.388 --> 00:18:19.391 position:50% align:center
When that rabbit locked eyes
with me, then jerked away,

00:18:19.474 --> 00:18:21.309 position:50% align:center
I knew what was going on.

00:18:21.393 --> 00:18:23.978 position:50% align:center
He was about to start
bitching about me.

00:18:24.062 --> 00:18:26.189 position:50% align:center
First, he wanted to make
sure I wasn't around,

00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:27.649 position:50% align:center
but I was around.

00:18:27.732 --> 00:18:29.984 position:50% align:center
He thought, "Oh, shit,
he's literally right there,"

00:18:30.068 --> 00:18:31.695 position:50% align:center
and panicked.

00:18:31.778 --> 00:18:34.406 position:50% align:center
I'm used to that kind
of treatment by now,

00:18:34.489 --> 00:18:36.908 position:50% align:center
so it's not that upsetting.

00:18:36.991 --> 00:18:38.910 position:50% align:center
What I do find upsetting

00:18:38.993 --> 00:18:42.080 position:50% align:center
is how long it took
for me to react at all.

00:18:46.292 --> 00:18:47.919 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] It feels like the
things that happen to me

00:18:48.003 --> 00:18:50.880 position:50% align:center
and my emotional response
to those things

00:18:50.964 --> 00:18:54.259 position:50% align:center
have somehow drifted
out of sync.

00:18:54.342 --> 00:18:57.053 position:50% align:center
I still feel the seed of rage,

00:18:57.137 --> 00:18:59.931 position:50% align:center
but it's been buried
by indifference.

00:19:00.015 --> 00:19:01.891 position:50% align:center
How's it going, Uramichi?

00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:04.561 position:50% align:center
Pretty good, Iketeru.
Please knock next time.

00:19:04.644 --> 00:19:06.604 position:50% align:center
Now, what brings ya here?

00:19:06.688 --> 00:19:10.442 position:50% align:center
The physicist Richard
Feynman. You know him?

00:19:10.525 --> 00:19:12.235 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Uh.

00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:14.446 position:50% align:center
Well, yeah. I've heard of him.

00:19:14.529 --> 00:19:18.116 position:50% align:center
He studied tiny particles
of light or whatever, right?

00:19:20.118 --> 00:19:21.828 position:50% align:center
[chuckles] Right.

00:19:21.911 --> 00:19:25.999 position:50% align:center
So, I only just found out
about him a little while ago...

00:19:26.082 --> 00:19:29.586 position:50% align:center
...and I laughed so hard
I could barely breathe.

00:19:29.669 --> 00:19:32.255 position:50% align:center
'Ca-Cause his nickname, it...

00:19:32.339 --> 00:19:35.425 position:50% align:center
It would be "Dick."

00:19:35.508 --> 00:19:36.676 position:50% align:center
Dick Feynman.

00:19:36.760 --> 00:19:38.428 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU laughing]

00:19:38.511 --> 00:19:39.804 position:50% align:center
Oh. Hey!

00:19:39.888 --> 00:19:42.515 position:50% align:center
If you guys are ready,
we should head on back.

00:19:47.437 --> 00:19:49.356 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Y'know Dick Shiner?

00:19:49.439 --> 00:19:50.565 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Wait. Wait.

00:19:50.648 --> 00:19:51.566 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Dick Lord?

00:19:51.649 --> 00:19:53.985 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU laughing]

00:19:54.069 --> 00:19:54.778 position:50% align:center
[EDEI]
Hm?

00:19:54.861 --> 00:19:56.279 position:50% align:center
Is something wrong?

